descript.abstract:
VW_ADDRESS is a spatial view that contains every address point from the Facilities Geodatabase and all of the associated address records. Every address point has at least one address, but a point can also have multiple addresses. An address can also have multiple address units, however this specific view does not contain address units.
Address points represent the geographic location of an address. There are multiple types of entities that an address point can represent besides just buildings. It is important to note the other types of entities that are represented by an address point. The field BLDG_CODE classifies what type of entity an address point represents. There are four different BLDG_CODE classifications that do not usually have a building at that location. These classifications are: PRIVATE VACANT, PUBLIC VACANT, INFRASTRUCTURE, and STORM WATER MANAGEMENT.
It is also important to note that this view contains both active and inactive addresses and points. Addresses and points are not deleted from the Facilities Geodatabase but are set to inactive once they are no longer valid.
descript.purpose: This entity is a spatial view created within ESRI's Geodatabase. It presents a logical view of the addresses for the user in their applications. It is created primarily to join the Address feature class, Address table and StreetName table to provide a comprehensive "virtual" feature class for labeling, searching and displaying.

Tax Account unique identifier for linking to assessment data. This tax account is populated from the physical parcel in which the related address point exists. An individual address may have a different tax account than the point it is related to. This occurs for condominiums and multi-account parcels.
